$interpreted: Juan Yun: Hey, our luck's not so bad. This boat's in good shape~
Tindoiimu: What's wrong?
Juan Yun: ...I have a request, if I may be so bold...
Juan Yun: Rumors are that the princess' sister is leading a group bent on complete eradication of all Alliance citizens...
Jihasaha: Hmph! You reap what you sow!
Juan Yun: No, those people are innocent. The same as your tribe. They don't deserve to die!
Jihasaha: One more word outta you...
Tindoiimu: So? What do you propose?
Juan Yun: I realize that at this moment, all anyone wants is revenge.
Juan Yun: But, I want to ask for you to please... help stop your sister from killing off my tribe.
Juan Yun: I will protect Insect Tribe royalty, if you help protect my tribe's people.
Juan Yun: I realize my request may cross the line, but I hope you three can understand.
Jihasaha: How dare you—
Tingko: Jihasaha!
Tingko: ...I know how you feel, I do, but...
Tingko: Princess...
Tindoiimu: ...Okay. If this means that we can work together, then I accept.
Tindoiimu: Do you have a pen and paper?
Juan Yun: ...I do!
Tindoiimu: Give this to my sister for me. Tell her it's an order.
Tingko: Of course! Leave it to me!
Tindoiimu: Jihasaha will go with you.
Tingko: Then we should be going, princess. And you need to promise to win the tournament. You show that Alliance!
Tindoiimu: Jihasaha?
Jihasaha: I know, I know, I'll take care of Tingko.
Tindoiimu: I was just going to say, "take care".
Jihasaha: ......
Tingko: Hehe...
Jihasaha: I don't know which one of you is more irritating. Let's go.
Juan Yun: So the princess can crack jokes after all? Maybe I'm rubbing off on you...?
Tindoiimu: ...Once I'm certain they've gotten out safely, I will take my butterfly back.
Juan Yun: You know, I'm a bit embarrassed to admit this, but...
Juan Yun: I always knew you were charming, but a woman with a sense of humor, that's just—
Tindoiimu: I hear sounds of battle...!
Juan Yun: Those people... they're bewitched!
Tindoiimu: And humans? Didn't you say there wouldn't be anybody here!?
Juan Yun: Yeah, that's what I thought...
Elio: Who are you!?
Tindoiimu: Deal with them first!
Tica: There's so many of them! Way too scary~!
Elio: Yeah, and I haven't seen any monsters...
Juan Yun: Li Hwa? What are you doing with the humans? And why are there so many bewitched?
Li Hwa: Juan Yun? And the Insect Tribe princess?
Li Hwa: Ah!
Elio: What's wrong?
Li Hwa: I'm sorry, I wasn't paying attention. I dropped all the medicine!
Tica: Aahh-choo! Agh, this smoke is making my nose all tingly!
Li Hwa: Just hold on, it'll disappear soon.
Li Hwa: (—Go, now!)
Juan Yun: Finally... Li Hwa, that smoke was really strong.
Li Hwa: How about less complaining and more helping. Go check if anyone is hurt, like that big guy over there!
Tindoiimu: (Ugh, more tigers...)
Tica: Does Pang need help again!? Hold on, I've got you!
Elio: Relax! If you use too many healing runes they'll have an adverse effect!
Juan Yun: ...So, these two are with you?
Li Hwa: Yep, they're top students from the Rune Academy. I invited them here with me for some academic exchange.
Juan Yun: Oh yeah, now I remember Soohyeon saying something about you studying at that human school.
Li Hwa: I've lived a long time—sometimes you've got to find new ways to keep busy. Can't put too many limits on yourself.
Juan Yun: How come you didn't enter through the port? Why pass through the lake?
Li Hwa: Well, it's got nothing to do with that tiger...
Li Hwa: ...Ah, what's the use. I'll tell you the truth.
Li Hwa: You two still remember the name Yao, right?
Juan Yun: You mean...
Li Hwa: Yeah, well this guy was part of that whole rebellion, and was exiled as a result. His name is Pang.
Li Hwa: We found him floating out by the port and brought him up onto our boat. I knew who he was right away.
Juan Yun: If he's caught being back in the Alliance like this...
Li Hwa: He'd most likely be executed.
Li Hwa: If it were up to me I'd report him to the Alliance Hall, but... he seems to be Tica's friend.
Tica: Not just a friend! Pang's part of my elite team of heroes! As team captain, I could never abandon a comrade!
Elio: Sorry, I don't really know what she's talking about either...
Li Hwa: We couldn't bring him through customs, so we had to find another way.
Li Hwa: But then the second we got off our boat, we ran into the bewitched...
Juan Yun: I see.
Li Hwa: So that's about the extent of it. I think it's your turn to tell me how you ended up here with the Insect Tribe princess.
Li Hwa: Are you trying to get out through Lake Lumina, as well?
Tindoiimu: ......
Juan Yun: No, we... we were just looking for somewhere quiet to talk.
Tindoiimu: (Is he protecting me?)
Li Hwa: You slimeball! You'll even go after the insect princess!?
Juan Yun: Not like that! I just meant... to listen to the princess' troubles, have a nice heart to heart~
Juan Yun: I would do the same for you, ma'am.
Li Hwa: Oh you're such a pain... always reminding me of my age. Well now your elder's gonna teach you some manners!
Juan Yun: Owww stop chasing me! Unfair advantage!
Juan Yun: —Still, you're pretty fast for a grandma.
Li Hwa: You little!
Elio: Li Hwa, we should really get going!
Tica: Ohhhh, I get it now!!
Tica: So, you guys are like... secret lovers!?
Elio: Tica! Don't make things worse!
Tica: They are! It's like something right out of a tragedy...
Tindoiimu: That's ridiculous. We're not lovers...
Elio: You'll have to excuse my friend, she's a little slow...
Juan Yun: So then, Princess, what would you call our relationship?
Li Hwa: Juan Yun! Could you stop hiding and flirting at the same time!
Elio: ...Ugh...
Pang: Agg..guhhh...
Tica: Oh! Comrade Pang! You're awake!
Pang: Gah... Tica? Why are you here? Where are Hestia and Puggi!?
Tica: Ah, Pang, calm down! Tica will tell you everything...
Pang: Well then, thank you all for rescuing me...
Pang: ...Now, what are you two doing here, if I may ask?
Tica: They're eloping!
Elio: Tica!
Pang: So, I seem to understand a bit of the situation...
Pang: I'm sorry for the trouble, qilin lord.
Juan Yun: It's nothing. But, you mentioned a mermaid?
Juan Yun: ...I was actually just late getting to the princess because of a mermaid and a... strange bird that had been brought to the Alliance Hall.
Pang: What!?
Juan Yun: I heard they were brought up by a fishing boat.
Juan Yun: One of them had fake travel permits. Mermaids have also been somewhat of a problem tribe lately, so they were brought to the hall.
Pang: (Those fake permits must have been mine!)
Pang: A problem tribe?
Juan Yun: ...The mermaids have been targeted by the Honey Badger Tribe lately.
Juan Yun: If she's left at the hall for too long, she might be given over to the honey badgers...
Pang: No! Then I must get to them immediately! Qilin Lord, is it possible for you to direct me to the Alliance Hall?
Juan Yun: Well...
Tica: Hold on, I'm super confused!
Tica: Is being sent to the Alliance Hall any different from being given to the honey badgers?
Pang: The honey badgers are ferocious. There's no saying what will happen if Hestia falls into their grasp.
Pang: I beg of you, my lord.
Juan Yun: But you're a fugitive. If you go to the Alliance Hall yourself...
Pang: I understand. You can rest assured I will not involve you in this.
Juan Yun: ...Alright. I can't stand by while someone is in need of assistance.
Juan Yun: Come with me, I will bring you to the hall.
Pang: My thanks.
Tica: Comrade Pang! I'll come along, too!
Tindoiimu: ...It's possible that you're overdoing it, Juan Yun. This could just make things worse for everyone...

Juan Yun: Isn't that a little like your situation?
...Yes, I'm aware, but I have to try and help. That is my nature.
Juan Yun: Forgive me.
Tindoiimu: ......
Elio: Is this okay, Li Hwa?
Li Hwa: If it's okay with them, it's okay with me. If you're worried, then why don't you tag along?
Elio: What about you?
Li Hwa: We've been on the road for ages. You might not be tired, but I am.
Li Hwa: I will rest here a bit first, then catch up. Don't worry about me.
